# Bitstream dual-runtime parity (UART / Simulation, dev / VSIX)

**NON-NEGOTIABLE:** Every Bitstream-related feature must behave correctly in **both** telemetry backends and ship the same in **dev** and **installed VSIX**.

## UART and Simulation (mutually exclusive)

Treat **Bitstream** (real COM / BS-framed firmware) and **Simulation** (external **bitstream-simulator** VS Code extension) as **first-class peers** — **never mixed in the UI**.

- Backend store: **`useBitstreamTelemetrySourceStore`** — **`uart`** (UI **Bitstream**) | **`simulator`**; no Auto mode.
- **Route:** webview publishes **`bitstream2/telemetry/route`**; bridge gates UART vs `inject-rx`; samples tagged **`origin`**: `uart` | `sim`.
- **Ingest:** **`shouldIngestTelemetryForRoute()`** + **`shouldAcceptBs2SampleOrigin()`** in `bitstreamTelemetryTransport.ts`.
- **Lifecycle:** **`telemetryModeLifecycle.ts`** on toolbar change (clear data, release COM → Simulator, sim **`idle`/`run`**).
- Full design: **`extension/docs/TELEMETRY_MODE_LIFECYCLE.md`**.
- **Restart bridge** after `SerialPortWebSocketBridge.ts` changes.

### Sensor configuration (SENSOR_CFG v2 / v2.1)

- **Apply path (webview, v0.1):** **`useSensorConfigController`** updates store as **local draft** only (`updatedAtMs: 0`). Wire **`SENSOR_CFG_SET`** restore is backlog.
- Protocol: **`extension/src/bitstream2/docs/SENSOR_CFG_V2.md`**.

### UI readiness (sensor settings deck)

- Use **`useSensorSettingsPanelReady`** — HELLO / handshake + WS ready; not serial snapshot alone.

### Testing matrix (minimum)

| Backend | Connect | Verify |
|--------|---------|--------|
| **Simulation** | `start:bridge` + external sim streaming + toolbar **Simulator** | Sine samples; deck unlocks; no COM open |
| **Bitstream** | COM open @ 921600 + toolbar **Bitstream** | Hardware EVT only; sim inject blocked |

| Environment | Verify |
|-------------|--------|
| **Vite dev** | Both rows above + mode switch clears mixed data |
| **Installed VSIX** | Same; **`extension/HOW_TO_RUN.md`** smoke checklist |

## VS Code webview detection

- **Do not** use **`T3DVSCodeUtils.isVsCodeMode()` alone**.
- **Use** **`isVsCodeExtensionWebview()`**, **`window.WEBVIEW_READY`**, **`window.__VSCODE_API__`**.

## Build

- **`npm run compile`** in **`extension/`** before packaging.
- Re-test **`.vsix`** after **`npm run package`** (no `@ternion/t3d` in this repo).

